1 packet Diced Chicken
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Fresh Fettuccine
½ bottle cream
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet red pesto
1 bag green beans
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
olive oil

• Boil the kettle
• Trim and halve green beans
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook green beans, diced chicken and seasoning, tossing, until cooked through, 3-4 mins
• Add spinach and cook until wilted, 1 min

• Pour boiling water into a saucepan over high heat. Season generously with salt
• Bring to boil, add fettuccine and cook until ‘al dente’, 3 mins. Drain and set aside
• Reduce frying pan to medium-low heat, then add cream (1/2 bottle for 2P /1 bottle for 4P), garlic paste, Parmesan
and chicken stock. Cook until slightly thickened, 2-3 mins

• Roughly chop almonds
• Add pasta and pesto to frying pan and toss to coat. Season with pepper
• Plate up chicken pasta
• Serve topped with almonds